The phenotype and frequency of various lymphoid immune cells in pigs were analyzed by flow cytometry. The frequency of mock-infected pig immune cells is shown separately (Table 1
). The lungs from PRRS-MLV+ Mtb WCL vaccinated pigs had a higher frequency (but not significant) of total lymphocytes (CD3+
 T cells) and CD4+ T cells at all PID (Table 2A and B). At PID 30, a significant increase in the frequency of CD8+ T cells was detected in the lungs of PRRS-MLV+ Mtb WCL vaccinated pigs compared to lungs from pigs inoculated with PRRS-MLV alone (Table 2C). An increased (but not significant) frequency of CD8+ T cells was also detected in the lungs at PID 15 and 60 (Table 2C). In addition, increased (but not significant) frequency of γδ T cells in the lungs of PRRS-MLV+ Mtb WCL vaccinated pigs was detected at all the PID (Table 2D). In contrast, the frequency of Tregs in the lungs of PRRS-MLV+ Mtb WCL vaccinated pigs was significantly less compared to the frequency of Tregs in the lungs of PRRS-MLV inoculated pigs at PID 15 (Table 2E).
